    <h1>Quick start</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This quick start helps you set up your online store and publish it on the Internet. All of the topics are described in further detail in other chapters of the manual. Simply click on the links to access more detailed information.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The quick start is divided into the chapters <a href="/en/basics/first-steps/quick-start#10">Initial settings</a>, <a href="/en/basics/first-steps/quick-start#270">Setting up the online store</a> and <a href="/en/basics/first-steps/quick-start#690">Setting up automatic processes</a>. Each chapter covers one aspect of setting up of your online store. Work through these chapters in the given order, as each chapter builds on the previous ones. The quick start aims to help you set up a functional online store as quickly as possible. As such, it only describes the most necessary functions.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>First, a preparatory subchapter lists any requirements or tasks that need to be completed before you begin. Second, additional subchapters describe how to set up the system. Each step of the process is explained in detail and is clearly laid out. A checklist gives you the chance to make sure that all of the necessary steps were carried out.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <a href="/en/basics/first-steps/quick-start#820">Final check</a> is an instrument to recheck everything before your plentymarkets system goes live. Check the settings very carefully so that potential customers do not become involuntary beta testers of your system, but rather bring in your first revenue. In addition, familiarise yourself with the basic legal conditions of electronic commerce and comply with these regulations. Otherwise, you might receive expensive warnings from your competitors.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="10">1. Initial settings</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This chapter provides information about the basic settings that need to be carried out in the <strong>Settings</strong> menu to set up a functional online store. You will learn how to create and manage user accounts, how to configure email settings and how to set up shipping and payment methods.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="20">1.1. Preparation</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Here you will find information about the most important requirements and preliminary tasks for configuring the initial settings. You will also learn which data is needed for the quick start.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="30">1.1.1. Install an appropriate browser</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Install Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox or Safari (Mac OS).</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Browser compatibility</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>plentymarkets functions best with the <a href="https://www.google.co.uk/intl/en/chrome/browser/desktop/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Chrome</a> browser. However, you can also access plentymarkets with <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-GB/firefox/products/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mozilla Firefox</a> or <a href="http://www.apple.com/uk/safari/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Safari (Mac OS)</a>. This limitation only applies to the admin area. Your online store can be accessed with all of the typical Internet browsers.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="40">1.1.2. Have your email account data ready</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You have to save your email access data in the system before plentymarkets can send emails from your email account. Therefore, have the account details at hand for the email address that should be used to send notifications to customers (e.g. <a href="mailto:info@mystore.com">info@mystore.com</a>). Use the same settings as in your email program (e.g. Outlook or Thunderbird).</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="50">1.1.3. Have your tracking URL ready</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Have the tracking URL of your shipping service provider at hand. Customers can use this link to track their orders online. The shipping service provider’s tracking URL has to be entered in the system in order for this to be possible. Ask the shipping service provider for the tracking URL. The website links of integrated shipping service providers can be found on the <a href="/en/order-processing/fulfilment/preparing-the-shipment#2500">Preparing the shipment</a> page of the manual.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="60">1.1.4. Have your access data ready and log in for the first time</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Have your plentymarkets access data at hand. You received this data via email. This is the URL of the test system, your user name and password. Use this data to log into the admin area of your plentymarkets system for the first time.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>First login:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Start your browser.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Find the URL that you received via email and enter this URL into the browser’s address line.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Use the access data to log into the admin area of your plentymarkets test system.<br>
→ The plentymarkets back end will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save a bookmark for your plentymarkets system.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="65">1.1.5. Allowing pop-ups</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In several areas of the back end, pop-ups are used to, e.g., offer documents for download. To ensure proper functionality, add your plentymarkets back end to your browser’s pop-up whitelist. To do so, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Open your browser.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the settings.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Go to the pop-up exception management.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the link <strong>https://[*.]plentymarkets-cloud-de.com:PID</strong> for aws01 and <strong>https://[*.]plentymarkets-cloud-ie.com:PID</strong> for aws02 in the exception list. Please replace <strong>PID</strong> with your plenty ID.<br>
→ The exception for your back end is added.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="70">1.2. Lock store</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Before you begin making changes to your online store, you should <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/online-store#lock-store">lock</a> it and redirect your visitors to a page with a service note while your store is under construction. Unlock your store again when you have finished making changes. Otherwise, you will not be able to receive orders. We recommend that you open the online store using the standard URL in another browser after each maintenance. Use this chance to check whether all your changes have been carried out correctly.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Locking the online store:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Online store » Lock store</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Lock store now</strong> to redirect customers to a page with a service note.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="80">1.3. Managing user accounts</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The admin area of your plentymarkets system is password protected and can only be accessed by registered users. Therefore, we will start by looking at how to create and manage user accounts. Go to <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/manage-users">System » Settings » User</a> to create and manage users. Every user is given an individual user account and is assigned to a user class. The user classes are preset and include specific rights. <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/manage-users#70">Roles</a> allow you to assign users to individual groups. Roles can also be used to assign rights to an entire group of users. First, we will describe how to create and manage users.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="90">1.3.1. Creating a new user</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A standard user with administrator rights is already available in your test system. User class: Admin. We recommend that you change this user account immediately and create your own password.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The administration area contains sensitive data and has to be efficiently protected from unauthorised access and hackers. Therefore, handle user accounts with great care and only use passwords with at least 8 characters.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Caution: Pay attention to the password strength!</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you try to save a weak password, then you will receive the <strong>error message</strong><strong>Code 900: The password entered is too weak!</strong> The password should always contain a mixture of lower-case letters, upper-case letters and numbers. Pay attention to the colour-coded bar and percentage in the system. If possible, use a password that has a "green" rating.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a new user:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New</strong>.<br>
→ The <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/manage-users#10">Create new user</a> window will open (image 1).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the <strong>User name</strong>, <strong>Actual name</strong> and <strong>Password</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Repeat the password.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the new user’s email address. This will allow the user to receive messages from the system.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a <strong>User class</strong> (see the configuration note below).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/basics/first-steps/assets/EN-Quick-Start-01.png" alt="EN Quick Start 01">
</div>
<div class="title">Figure 1. creating a new user</div>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Classes and their rights</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/manage-users#10">user class</a> contains specific user rights. For example, the class <strong>Admin</strong> contains all of the rights without limitation. At least one user must be an admin. This is because only admins are authorised to manage and edit other user accounts without restriction. Use the class <strong>Variable</strong> to set up individual rights for a user. This allows you to give variable users the exact read and write permissions that they need. The classes <strong>Callcenter</strong>, <strong>API</strong>, <strong>Logistics</strong> and <strong>Blog</strong> have limited rights.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="100">1.3.2. Editing a user</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as follows to edit a user.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing a user account:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Open user</strong>.<br>
→ The user will open in a new tab (image 2).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out additional settings as desired. For further information, refer to the explanations on the <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/manage-users#20">Editing users</a> page of the manual.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/basics/first-steps/assets/EN-Quick-Start-02.png" alt="EN Quick Start 02">
</div>
<div class="title">Figure 2. editing a user</div>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Password is saved</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The password that you entered when creating your user account will not be visible in the editing mode later on but it is saved. You do not have to reenter the password when editing the user account.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="105">1.3.3. Setting a user as owner</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Owner</strong> tab, determine the areas the user should be owner of.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting a user as owner:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Open user</strong>.<br>
→ The user will open in a new tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Owner</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the areas the user should own. <br>
→ To use the plentymarkets stock management system, place a check mark next to <strong>incoming items</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="110">1.3.4. Deleting a user</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>There are two ways to delete a user:</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting a user account:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the user that you want to delete (image 2).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete user account</strong> on the right side of the header.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Confirm</strong> your decision to delete the user.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting several user accounts:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the user accounts.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Group function</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the <strong>Delete</strong> function.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Apply</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Confirm</strong> your decision to delete the users.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="120">1.4. Configuring email settings</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Not only can your plentymarkets system send notifications to administrators, it can also send automatic <a href="/en/crm/sending-emails">emails</a> to your customers. The system automatically generates order and shipping confirmations, dunning letters and other notifications and sends them to customers.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="130">1.4.1. Entering email access data</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You have to enter your <a href="/en/crm/sending-emails#100">access data</a> into the system before plentymarkets can send emails on your behalf from your email account. Use the same settings as in your email program (e.g. Outlook or Thunderbird).</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Entering email access data:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Email » Access data</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pay attention to the explanations given in table 1 and carry out the settings as desired.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
