<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="140">1.4.2. Setting up the email information service</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the <a href="/en/crm/sending-emails#700">Information service</a> to have more control over the emails that are sent by the system. This function can send all outgoing emails as blind copies (BCC) to an email address of your choice. It can also send an email notification every time a new order is placed in your online store. You need to know which email address the information service should send emails to.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up the information service:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Email » Information service</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the email address.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>YES</strong> to activate the information service for the address.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Select <strong>NO</strong> to deactivate the information service.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="150">1.4.3. Setting up email templates</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>plentymarkets creates all emails based on <a href="/en/crm/sending-emails#1200">Templates</a>. This section teaches you how to create email templates or edit existing templates as needed. The section <a href="/en/basics/first-steps/quick-start#690">Setting up automatic processes</a> teaches you how to have emails sent whenever specific events occur and how to automatically send emails at specific times of day.</p>
