<div class="paragraph subhead">
<p>Inserting template functions and template variables into email templates</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In plentymarkets, <a href="/en/crm/sending-emails#1200">email templates</a> not only consist of text but also of <a href="/en/crm/sending-emails#1300">template functions and template variables</a>. When plentymarkets sends emails, it automatically replaces the variables with the corresponding content. The customer’s name will appear instead of the variable <strong>$Name[1]</strong>. The customer’s email address will appear instead of <strong>$Email</strong>. The order number will appear instead of the variable <strong>$OrderID</strong>.</p>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/basics/first-steps/assets/EN-Quick-Start-03.png" alt="EN Quick Start 03">
</div>
