<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can define upper and lower limits by entering data into the fields <strong>Minimum value</strong> and <strong>Maximum value</strong>. Also check whether you need shipping profiles that go beyond the defined upper and lower limits. For example, if you limit a shipping profile to the maximum value of 200 EUR, then you will need another shipping profile so that an order of more than 200 EUR can actually be delivered.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="220">1.6. Setting up payment methods</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up payment methods so that customers can pay for their purchases in your online store.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="230">1.6.1. Activating payment methods</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <a href="/en/order-processing/payment">System » Orders » Payment » Payment methods</a> to see and configure the payment methods that are currently integrated in plentymarkets. Some payment methods, e.g. cash in advance or invoice, can be used without the help of a payment provider. However, many payment methods in this menu will require you to work with a payment provider.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Closing contracts with payment providers</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It can take time to set up an interface with a payment provider. Decide which providers you want to work with and contact them as early as possible to avoid any delays.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following <a href="/en/order-processing/payment/managing-payment-methods#40">payment methods</a> can be used without the help of a payment provider:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Cash in advance</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Cash payment upon pickup</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Invoice</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Debit (manual processing is possible in most cases. Consult your local bank.)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating payment methods:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Orders » Payment » Methods</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the option <strong>Also show inactive</strong> since you have not activated any payment methods yet.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the folders <strong>International</strong> and <strong>DE</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the <strong>Payment method</strong> or <strong>Payment provider</strong> that you want to activate.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired. Pay attention to the information given in table 6.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the option <strong>Active</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
