<h2 id="270">2. Setting up the online store</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This chapter of the quick start provides information about the settings that need to be carried out in plentymarkets to set up the online store before you begin actively working with the system. It describes all the necessary steps such as building the item catalogue and creating the categories.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="280">2.1. Preparation</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Here you will find information about the most important preliminary tasks for setting up the online store. This page also specifies which data will be needed for the quick start and the basic settings of your online store.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In addition, we have also created a video tutorial that covers the same topic:</p>
</div>
<div class="videoblock">
<div class="content">
<iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/190868520" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="290">2.1.1. Define categories and subcategories</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Categories help you structure your product portfolio and organise the items in your online store. Take a moment to think about which categories and subcategories you want to display in your online store. It is best to prepare this information in a document before you begin.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="300">2.1.2. Compile the terms and conditions</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Compile your terms and conditions into a document. You can refer to standard texts when creating your terms and conditions. Have the texts checked by a specialised solicitor.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="310">2.1.3. Obtain a legally sound sample of customers' cancellation rights</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Legally sound cancellation rights have to fulfil certain requirements with regards to form and content. Therefore, procure a current, legally sound sample.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/extras">Services</a> chapter lists several partners who can help you create legally sound texts.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="320">2.2. Setting up a catalogue of items</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>All items and variations are listed in the <a href="/en/item/managing-items">Item » Edit item</a> menu. You can search for and edit the items here. In new plentymarkets systems, you will find some test items in this menu. Items can be edited directly in the list by clicking on the icons in the <strong>Procedures</strong> column. These procedures are described in table 8. Use the filters on the left to search for items. These filters are described in further detail on the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#350">Searching items and variations</a> page. A bit of preparation is necessary before putting the first items into the system, e.g. deleting the sample items and creating categories and attributes.</p>
