<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="540">2.3.2. Categories of the type Content: Editing texts</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>All <a href="/en/item/managing-categories">categories</a> of the type <strong>Content</strong> can be edited in the same way. This quick start uses the <strong>homepage</strong> to illustrate all of the necessary steps.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The integrated <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/cms#web-design-tools-editor">editor</a> is used to format all texts in your plentymarkets system. It is handled just like a word processing software. New texts can be entered by typing them in or by inserting them using the clipboard. Click on the import icon to insert texts from Word or similar software without the superfluous code. All texts can be manually formatted with the editor’s icons. Alternatively, you can use the predefined styles (recommended) to create a consistent layout. All of these templates can be changed in one central location later on. Global changes, e.g. font size or colour, will automatically be transferred to all of the text passages that are linked to these templates.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In particular, use the templates <strong>Heading 1</strong> to <strong>Heading 3</strong> to mark and highlight important text passages for search engines. For better readability of your texts, you should distinguish between <strong>ENTER</strong> for a new paragraph and <strong>SHIFT+ENTER</strong> for a new line.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Changing styles</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Editing the styles requires some knowledge of CSS. They can be edited in the <strong>CSSContent</strong> template of the <strong>CMS » Web design » Layout » CSS</strong> menu. Edit this template carefully and only after you have saved the original template. This will allow you to restore it should this become necessary.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing categories of the type Content:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Categories</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the category <strong>callisto_light_3_5</strong> in the directory tree on the left. → The category will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the category <strong>Homepage</strong>.<br>
→ The category will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Make sure that the category type <strong>Content</strong> is selected in the <strong>Settings</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Description 1</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Edit the content to meet your needs.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="550">2.3.3. Categories of the type Content: Inserting images</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Images have to be uploaded to the webserver before they can be inserted into categories. Images can be uploaded in a category’s <a href="/en/item/managing-categories#10">Documents</a> tab. Alternatively, images can be uploaded in the menu <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/cms#image-gallery">CMS » Image gallery</a>. Proceed as described below to upload and define category images.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Uploading and defining category images:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Categories</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the category.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Documents</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Upload the image by clicking on <strong>Upload files</strong> or by using the drag &amp; drop function.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Point your cursor over the image.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the image.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Define image 1</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The image will be outlined in red and designated with the number 1.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Upload the second category image the same way and click on <strong>Define image 2</strong>. Deselect a category image by placing a check mark for the image and clicking on <strong>Define image 1</strong> or <strong>Define image 2</strong> a second time.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It is not possible to click on a button that is greyed out in the toolbar until you have selected one or more images. By selecting images with check marks, you can see a preview, download or delete several images at the same time.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Displaying category images in the online store</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Only image 1 is displayed in the online store by default. An <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/cms-syntax#basics-if">if-query</a> was added to the <strong>ItemViewCategoriesList</strong> template with the template variable <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/cms-syntax#web-design-navigation">$CurrentCategoryImageUrl</a>. You have to add a second if-query to the template in order for image 2 to be displayed.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="560">2.3.4. Categories of the type Content: Inserting text links</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It is also possible to insert links into your categories.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A text-based link consists of two parts: the visible part of the link, i.e. the title or anchor text, and the invisible target of the link. You create a link by highlighting any text and saving a target for it. In plentymarkets, you can do this using just one command from your editor window.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>An example of a valid target address is <a href="https://www.google.co.uk/" class="bare">https://www.google.co.uk/</a>. This is an external target. If you want to create links to internal pages of your online store, then use template variables and functions to specify the target of a link.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following example teaches you how to create an internal text link from the homepage to a category.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Inserting a text link:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Categories</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the category you want to link to.<br>
→ The category ID is displayed in the upper toolbar. In our example, this is the ID 3. Note the ID.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Copy the URL function, i.e. your link’s target. In this case, this is <strong>&#123;&#37; Link(3) &#37;&#125;</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the homepage.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Description 1</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the desired location and enter a suitable text, e.g. "Open link…​".</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Highlight the text.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Link</strong> in the middle toolbar.<br>
→ The <strong>Link</strong> window will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Insert the content (i.e. the link’s target as a template function) into the <strong>URL</strong> field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>&lt;other&gt;</strong> as the <strong>Protocol</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>OK</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For external targets, enter the absolute URL into the <strong>URL</strong> field and select a <strong>protocol</strong>, e.g. https://.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It is also possible to insert text links directly into the source code. Simply open the category, click on <strong>Description 1</strong> and click on <strong>Source</strong> in the middle toolbar. The following examples show the source code for an external link that opens in a new tab and for an internal text link that opens in the same tab in the browser.</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>External link<br>
<strong>&lt;a href="https://www.plentymarkets.co.uk/"target="_blank"&gt;plentymarkets&lt;/a&gt;</strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Internal text link<br>
<strong>&lt;a href="https://www.plentymarkets.co.uk/"Settings&lt;/a&gt;</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can also link individual items as the target of a link. These can also be inserted using <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/cms-syntax#web-design">template variables and functions</a>. The following table lists several important template functions:</p>
