<h4 id="590">2.4.1. Selecting the URL structure</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the settings in the <strong>System » Client » Select client » SEO » URL structure</strong> menu to influence the <strong>structure of category and item URLs</strong> in your online store. The URL structure is relevant for search engine optimisation (SEO). In general, the URL should contain information that is relevant for finding your items. Avoid overloading your online store URL with information. If a URL is too long and contains too many keywords, search engines might interpret it as forbidden manipulation.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>No one can say with absolute certainty what the ideal balance is between providing a short URL and one that contains a wealth of detail. Read through the <strong>SEO</strong> chapter before you decide on a URL structure for your online store. It explains the different components that make up a URL and illustrates various types of URLs. This will help you or your search engine advisor make an informed decision.</p>
</div>
