<h4 id="640">2.4.6. Entering SEO meta data</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The settings in the menu <strong>System » Client » Select client » SEO » Meta data</strong> are relevant for search engine optimisation. Meta data is information on a web page that is accessible to search engines but is invisible (or only indirectly visible) to visitors.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The basic data you enter here will be complemented by further information entered on other pages, e.g. the detailed views of your items. The amount of information that should to be provided in this general part also depends on how detailed and descriptive your categories and item names are. Therefore, no general advice can be given. We recommend that you consult an expert in search engine optimisation or independently observe the listing of your pages in search engines on a regular basis.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In general, it is important not to waste space in the meta data with unspecific texts such as <strong>Welcome to our homepage</strong>. Instead, you should think about the most important search terms and possible synonyms or alternative spellings in advance.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The most important entry for search engines is the page title, since search engines give it special preference. Page titles will only be processed up to a certain length and longer titles will be cut off. Therefore, position important keywords at the front of the title (&lt; 60 characters). The page title is usually displayed in search results and seen by potential customers.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Entering SEO meta data:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » SEO » Meta data</strong>.</p>
